main event: A UFO report from Project Blue Book, an official U.S. Air Force program, describing a sighting in Wilmington, Delaware on 9th May 1959 at 21:30Z.
interesting points: The UFO was described as round, small like a nickel, and moved away very fast with a bright light.
The object was observed moving from south to north vertically, then east out of sight, and it was visible for approximately 3 minutes.
The observer, Lt. Henry L. Isenberg, mentioned the presence of many commercial type aircraft in the area.
Lt. Isenberg was hesitant about calling but kept trying to get the authorities to send up a plane to intercept the UFO.
The report was classified as UNCLAS and the weather conditions at the time of the sighting were clear.
sighted object: round, small object with bright light
witnesses: Lt. Henry L. Isenberg, 2D LT, Officer of the Day
